<br>
Personally I believe a 60 ranger with a good bow, trueshot, and some AA skills is probably the hardest duel.  Their range with most bows is well outside most spells' range and their damage in a single shot is, at least from what I've seen, about as high as you hitting them with a 2hander.  They have a naturally higher atk rating than paladins with a 2h because oddly enough their skill cap is higher 250 to 225 as well as their buffs adding additional atk and so jousting, opposer's ac to your atk ratio you're gonna be coming out about even.<br>
<br>
